draw((10,0)--(12,0),dashed);
label("$R$",(10,0),S);
label("$r$",(5,0),S);
[/asy]

Then $OP = OX + XP = OX + OX = 2OX,$ so $\frac{r^2 \pi}{R^2 \pi} = \frac{r^2}{4r^2} = \boxed{\frac{1}{4}}.$

